1Ô∏è‚É£ Port Checking Logic (Backend)

PortChecker.java

package com.accesschecker;

import java.net.InetSocketAddress;
import java.net.Socket;

public class PortChecker {

    private static final int TIMEOUT_MS = 3000;

    public static String check(String host, int port) {
        try (Socket socket = new Socket()) {
            socket.connect(new InetSocketAddress(host, port), TIMEOUT_MS);
            return "SUCCESS: " + host + ":" + port + " is reachable";
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return "FAILED : " + host + ":" + port + " ‚Üí " + e.getMessage();
        }
    }
}

‚úî Uses TCP socket connection
‚úî Works for app servers, DB ports, APIs, etc.


